♪

24:26.684 --> 24:28.450
Clément: Her name is
Alexandra Lafayette.

24:28.452 --> 24:30.953
Her husband came home last
night and startled an intruder,

24:30.955 --> 24:32.121
who escaped.

24:32.123 --> 24:34.123
But that's when he found her.

24:34.959 --> 24:36.058
She's French?

24:36.060 --> 24:39.361
My inspectors didn't
immediately connect her

24:39.363 --> 24:42.698
with the American women
until they saw this.

24:42.700 --> 24:46.602
♪

24:48.973 --> 24:50.506
Mae: Looks like a butterfly.

24:50.508 --> 24:52.207
I don't understand.

24:52.209 --> 24:56.311
He filled her stomach
full of dead butterflies.

24:56.313 --> 24:57.813
Yeah, but it doesn't look
like any kind of butterfly

24:57.815 --> 24:59.181
I've ever seen before.

24:59.183 --> 25:01.583
He didn't take the time to
stage her body at the scene.

25:01.585 --> 25:04.486
As I said, Madame Lafayette's
husband walked in on him.

25:04.488 --> 25:07.256
Yeah, but how did he not know that
she was living with her husband?

25:07.258 --> 25:09.424
I mean, do you think that he
didn't have a chance to ask her?

25:09.426 --> 25:11.360
Or maybe he no longer cares.

25:11.362 --> 25:12.795
Why wouldn't he care?

25:12.797 --> 25:14.029
It's a terrible risk.

25:14.031 --> 25:16.832
Because maybe he doesn't
have <i> time</i> to care

25:16.834 --> 25:18.967
if his victims are American or French.

25:18.969 --> 25:20.736
And now any vulnerable woman will do.

25:20.738 --> 25:23.005
He has to finish what he
started before it's too late.

25:23.007 --> 25:24.807
Too late for what, Mademoiselle?

25:24.809 --> 25:27.009
Well, for one thing, he
knows that we're on to him.

25:27.011 --> 25:29.578
And it's just a matter of time
before we shut him down, right?

25:29.580 --> 25:31.747
Right, but I think there's something
else applying pressure to him,

25:31.749 --> 25:33.348
forcing him to accelerate his mission,

25:33.350 --> 25:34.616
its statement.

25:34.618 --> 25:37.286
And this time, it's his
butterflies in the stomach.

25:37.288 --> 25:39.288
That is what he was trying to say.

25:39.290 --> 25:41.557
I think we've been
looking at these murders

25:41.559 --> 25:43.258
like they're just rehearsals.

25:43.260 --> 25:45.594
But maybe they're the main event.

25:45.596 --> 25:47.162
How do you figure?

25:47.164 --> 25:49.698
I think our visceral
reaction to the brutality here

25:49.700 --> 25:51.633
is keeping us from seeing the scene

25:51.635 --> 25:53.235
from the unsub's point of view.

25:53.237 --> 25:56.104
I have butterflies in my stomach.

25:58.209 --> 26:01.944
I have my heart in my hands.

26:01.946 --> 26:03.846
I lost my head.

26:03.848 --> 26:05.214
♪

26:05.216 --> 26:06.682
And I am blinded by love.

26:06.684 --> 26:07.883
This is not love.

26:07.885 --> 26:09.885
This is vicious and cruel.

26:09.887 --> 26:12.788
Yes, but, you see, they aren't
either of those things to our unsub.

26:12.790 --> 26:14.489
To him, these crime scenes are a way

26:14.491 --> 26:16.091
for him to try and express himself.

26:16.093 --> 26:18.393
Yeah, and you think that
he's trying to express himself

26:18.395 --> 26:20.596
to this idealized American woman?

26:20.598 --> 26:21.864
I do.

26:21.866 --> 26:23.866
I think he is trying to tell
her how she makes him feel.

26:23.868 --> 26:26.435
It's like a series of
sick, twisted valentines.

26:26.437 --> 26:27.736
So you don't think she's a target.

26:27.738 --> 26:29.571
I think she's the
object of his affections,

26:29.573 --> 26:31.573
and he will try and
reach out to her for sure.

26:31.575 --> 26:34.209
But if and when she
rejects his affections...

26:34.211 --> 26:36.111
He will feel betrayed by love

26:36.113 --> 26:38.146
and ultimately lash out on her.

26:38.148 --> 26:40.382
Let us presume you're
correct, Agent Seger.

26:40.384 --> 26:42.251
If we can't find this man,

26:42.253 --> 26:44.253
perhaps we find this woman.

26:44.255 --> 26:47.656
I just know if she will be
any easier to find than him.

26:47.658 --> 26:50.759
Yeah, but let's not forget
about these guys here.

26:50.761 --> 26:52.294
I mean...

26:52.296 --> 26:56.198
Something tells me that this
butterfly effect may just...

26:56.200 --> 26:57.699
how did you say it, Commissaire Clément?

26:57.701 --> 26:59.234
Shake the fruit out of the tree?

26:59.236 --> 27:01.403
♪

27:02.239 --> 27:04.973
Monty: Say hello to my little friend.

27:04.975 --> 27:08.076
<i>Udaspes folus... </i> a.k.a.
the grass demon butterfly.

27:08.078 --> 27:11.346
Not only does he not normally
reside in your intestines,

27:11.348 --> 27:14.149
but he's a non-native to
the European continent.

27:14.151 --> 27:16.418
He prefers India and southeast Asia.

27:16.420 --> 27:18.921
So our unsub either gets hold
of these demon butterflies

27:18.923 --> 27:20.722
by importing them or stealing them.

27:20.724 --> 27:22.791
Let's go with what's
behind door number two.

27:22.793 --> 27:25.661
Import records show a delivery
was made to the Paris area

27:25.663 --> 27:29.197
about nine months ago, to <i>
Maison des papillons,</i>

27:29.199 --> 27:31.400
which is literally
"house o' butterflies."

27:31.402 --> 27:33.268
Then about a week ago, a
trespassing charge was filed

27:33.270 --> 27:34.403
and then dropped

27:34.405 --> 27:37.272
against a 42-year-old
man named Paul Mossier.

27:37.274 --> 27:39.207
Wait a second. That
name sounds familiar.

27:39.209 --> 27:40.642
That last name... Mossier.

27:40.644 --> 27:43.111
When I followed up with
the Boulanger family

27:43.113 --> 27:45.714
and what's become of the
le Lion de l'eau company,

27:45.716 --> 27:47.849
there was a dispute over inheritance

27:47.851 --> 27:50.485
that was filed 20 years
ago by Killian Mossier.

27:50.487 --> 27:53.655
Could be an uncle on
Madame Boulanger's side.

27:53.657 --> 27:55.590
I'm not big on coincidence.

27:55.592 --> 27:56.692
Yeah, right.

27:56.694 --> 27:59.027
And if Paul <i> is</i>
connected to the family,

27:59.029 --> 28:00.529
then that's how he
gets the murder weapons.

28:00.531 --> 28:03.732
Monty, what else can you tell
us about this Paul Mossier?

28:03.734 --> 28:05.033
He's got a bit of a record

28:05.035 --> 28:06.802
dating back the last several years.

28:06.804 --> 28:09.137
Various assaults, disorderly conduct.

28:09.139 --> 28:10.973
Then it says here that following

28:10.975 --> 28:13.342
an attempted assault
on a police officer,

28:13.344 --> 28:16.111
Paul Mossier was remanded
to a psychiatric hospital.

28:16.113 --> 28:18.013
He's supposed to be an in-patient

28:18.015 --> 28:19.614
at l'Institut du Pinel.

28:19.616 --> 28:21.316
Clara and I will check it out...

28:21.318 --> 28:23.652
While you two stay
here and try to identify

28:23.654 --> 28:27.789
the American woman who's the
focus of our unsub's attention.

28:29.126 --> 28:31.059
♪

28:32.879 --> 28:34.478
- <i>Bonjour.
- Bonjour.</i>

28:34.480 --> 28:36.313
<i>Je suis l'officier Seger.</i>

28:36.315 --> 28:38.582
<i>C'est l'unité du Chef Garrett.</i>

28:38.584 --> 28:40.351
<i>Nous sommes du FBI.</i>

28:40.353 --> 28:43.220
<i>Nous aimerions parler avec
Monsieur Paul Mossier.</i>

28:43.222 --> 28:44.922
- Je vais voir.
- Excuse me.

28:44.924 --> 28:45.715
You are looking for Paul?

28:46.137 --> 28:47.425
That's right. And you are?

28:47.434 --> 28:50.469
Dr. Alain Gilles, clinical
director of behavioral health.

28:50.471 --> 28:52.237
Is Paul Mossier a patient here?

28:52.239 --> 28:55.407
I'm sorry, but, uh, why does
the FBI want to speak to him?

28:55.409 --> 28:58.910
His name's come up with regards
to an ongoing investigation.

28:59.747 --> 29:01.580
You think he has something to do

29:01.582 --> 29:04.216
with the American women
who have been murdered.

29:05.085 --> 29:06.651
We need to speak to him.

29:06.653 --> 29:09.521
Paul was released from our
supervision over two weeks ago.

29:09.523 --> 29:11.556
When he was remanded to this facility,

29:11.558 --> 29:12.958
what was his diagnosis?

29:12.960 --> 29:15.827
I'm truly not at liberty to
share those details with you.

29:15.829 --> 29:17.729
Were you his primary therapist?

29:17.731 --> 29:19.564
Yes, myself and Dr. Bernard.

29:19.566 --> 29:20.665
But to be honest,

29:20.667 --> 29:23.101
Paul showed the greatest
signs of improvement

29:23.103 --> 29:24.236
over the last months

29:24.238 --> 29:26.605
while working with
one of our volunteers.

29:26.607 --> 29:28.473
She, uh, used art therapy.

29:31.078 --> 29:32.978
Jack: Is this her?

29:32.980 --> 29:35.781
Yes. Her name is Amy Wallace.

29:35.783 --> 29:38.350
Amy's an American, isn't she?

29:38.352 --> 29:40.619
- Yes, she is.
- May we speak with her?

29:40.621 --> 29:42.554
Unfortunately, she is no longer here.

29:42.556 --> 29:45.056
She left about a month ago.

29:45.058 --> 29:49.594
♪

29:50.631 --> 29:53.298
Did she see this before she left?

29:53.300 --> 29:54.466
No.

29:54.468 --> 29:56.802
Paul took her absence very hard.

29:56.804 --> 29:58.770
He comes from a family of craftsmen,

29:58.772 --> 30:01.139
but due to his struggles
with mental health,

30:01.141 --> 30:02.107
they rejected him.

30:02.109 --> 30:04.009
Amy was probably the first person

30:04.011 --> 30:05.877
to help him realize his potential.

30:05.879 --> 30:07.879
But this hospital felt
comfortable releasing him

30:07.881 --> 30:09.581
despite his known aggressive tendencies

30:09.583 --> 30:11.950
and this suggestion
of a violent fantasy?

30:11.952 --> 30:13.919
It's not what I would have preferred,

30:13.921 --> 30:15.287
but Paul had improved enough

30:15.289 --> 30:17.222
that we could no longer
hold him involuntarily.

30:17.224 --> 30:20.992
Do you know if Paul tried to
contact Amy after his release?

30:20.994 --> 30:22.894
As a matter of fact, he did, yes.

30:22.896 --> 30:24.496
He asked for her address.

30:24.498 --> 30:26.364
And that's when someone mentioned
that she had gotten engaged

30:26.366 --> 30:28.700
and that she was returning
to the United States.

30:28.702 --> 30:31.036
But you don't know if or
when she returned to the U.S.?

30:31.038 --> 30:32.637
No, I do not, I'm sorry.

30:33.974 --> 30:36.174
Thank you, doctor.

30:36.176 --> 30:37.642
Sure.

30:37.644 --> 30:39.778
Thank you.

30:39.780 --> 30:42.080
We need to find Amy Wallace... now.

30:42.082 --> 30:43.515
♪

30:47.421 --> 30:49.821
Paul?

30:49.823 --> 30:50.989
<i>Bonjour,</i> Amy.

30:50.991 --> 30:53.592
I didn't know you knew where I lived.

30:53.594 --> 30:55.627
Well, I apologize for not calling

30:55.629 --> 30:57.562
before dropping by like this.

30:57.564 --> 30:58.997
No, it's fine. I...

30:58.999 --> 31:01.299
Just thought you were the movers.

31:01.301 --> 31:04.769
They're already an hour late,
and I'm moving back home.

31:04.771 --> 31:05.804
Oh.

31:05.806 --> 31:08.073
But it's really good to see you.

31:08.075 --> 31:10.575
It's really good to see you, too.

31:10.577 --> 31:12.911
Sorry I haven't had a chance to visit.

31:12.913 --> 31:14.513
It's been a busy time.

31:14.515 --> 31:15.580
Well...

31:15.582 --> 31:17.849
I'm no longer a patient at the hospital.

31:17.851 --> 31:20.852
- Wonderful.
- [Chuckles]

31:20.854 --> 31:23.622
And you're still working on
the things we were focused on?

31:23.624 --> 31:24.890
Oh, yes, I have.

31:24.892 --> 31:27.425
I-I need to show you something.

31:27.427 --> 31:28.527
Okay.

31:28.529 --> 31:30.762
Uh, but, uh, it's not here.

31:30.764 --> 31:33.899
So I need to take you... to see it.

31:33.901 --> 31:36.001
Paul, like I said, I can't leave.

31:36.003 --> 31:38.203
I'm still waiting for the movers.

31:38.205 --> 31:40.405
I...

31:40.407 --> 31:44.242
I've been working really hard, Amy.

31:44.244 --> 31:45.710
Please...

31:45.712 --> 31:47.245
Come...

31:47.247 --> 31:49.114
With me.

31:50.517 --> 31:51.650
Okay.

31:51.652 --> 31:53.885
Let me just grab my coat.

31:53.887 --> 31:56.354
Okay.

31:57.190 --> 31:59.324
[Screaming]

31:59.326 --> 32:01.359
[Gasping]

32:01.361 --> 32:04.729
Paul, stop, stop!

32:04.731 --> 32:06.231
Please.

32:06.233 --> 32:07.933
I'm not going to hurt you.

32:07.935 --> 32:09.267
I promise.

32:09.269 --> 32:12.170
We're just playing <i>le
jeu d'évanouissement.</i>

32:12.172 --> 32:14.239
It's a fainting game.

32:14.241 --> 32:20.178
Good night, my love.

32:21.715 --> 32:24.516
♪

32:30.470 --> 32:32.337
[Indistinct conversation]

32:33.173 --> 32:36.004
My inspectors have searched the
building and outer perimeter.

32:36.154 --> 32:38.721
There's no sign of Paul
Mossier or Amy Wallace.

32:38.723 --> 32:40.289
No sign of a struggle.

32:40.291 --> 32:41.190
I'm not surprised.

32:41.192 --> 32:42.591
If we're right, at this moment,

32:42.593 --> 32:44.293
Paul's intention is not to hurt Amy,

32:44.295 --> 32:46.195
but to try and impress
her with what he's done.

32:46.197 --> 32:47.830
So he would have incapacitated her

32:47.832 --> 32:51.300
in order to transport her someplace
he feels safe and comfortable.

32:51.302 --> 32:53.569
I cannot believe his
intention is not to kill her.

32:53.571 --> 32:55.438
She could already be dead

32:55.440 --> 32:57.073
and he's taken her body
somewhere to pose it.

32:57.075 --> 32:59.742
Believe it or not, Paul's
actually trying to woo Amy,

32:59.744 --> 33:02.011
which means we have
time, but you are right.

33:02.013 --> 33:04.280
Eventually, Amy will
see what Paul has done,

33:04.282 --> 33:06.248
and she will absolutely reject him.

33:06.250 --> 33:07.383
And that's when he kills her.

33:07.385 --> 33:09.585
The question is, where did he take her?

33:09.587 --> 33:10.653
[Cellphone rings]

33:10.655 --> 33:11.687
[Cellphone beeps]

33:11.689 --> 33:13.155
Simmons, what do you got?

33:13.157 --> 33:14.390
At 2:37 P.M.,

33:14.392 --> 33:16.959
Alexandra Lafayette called
for roadside assistance.

33:16.961 --> 33:19.195
When the tow-truck
driver finally showed up,

33:19.197 --> 33:20.396
he sees another tow truck

33:20.398 --> 33:22.498
hauling away appears to
be Alexandra's vehicle.

33:22.500 --> 33:24.600
Mae: That was under the bridge
near the <i> rue de l'Étoile,</i>

33:24.602 --> 33:26.535
and Monty's got a hook
up to the CCTV cameras

33:26.537 --> 33:28.971
at the intersection running
both north and south of there.

33:28.973 --> 33:30.606
Let me patch you in, boss.

33:30.608 --> 33:33.742
I was able to spot our unsub's
new ride, which is a tow truck,

33:33.744 --> 33:36.312
and he's clearly got
Alexandra's car hooked up to it.

33:36.314 --> 33:38.647
He's heading northbound on
the <i> rue d'Étoile.</i>

33:38.649 --> 33:40.382
But I ran all the CCTV footage.

33:40.384 --> 33:41.784
I lost them heading north-northeast

33:41.786 --> 33:43.419
toward the Tremblay-en-France.

33:43.421 --> 33:45.855
I don't think he'd take her
completely out of the city, Jack.

33:45.857 --> 33:48.023
That's a pretty industrial area.
It's a good place to lay low.

33:48.025 --> 33:49.959
But there's no record of a Paul Mossier

33:49.961 --> 33:52.128
owning or leasing
property out in that area.

33:52.130 --> 33:53.195
Simmons: Well, it's got to be connected

33:53.197 --> 33:54.330
to Killian Mossier somehow.

33:54.332 --> 33:56.265
Mae and I will check the records again.

33:56.267 --> 33:59.335
We need to set up a command
post out near the airport.

34:05.643 --> 34:09.777
[ <i>Jazz music plays</i> ]

34:15.953 --> 34:20.121
[ <i>Woman singing in French</i> ]

34:24.661 --> 34:25.960
[Gasps]

34:25.963 --> 34:28.063
Paul? Where am I?

34:28.065 --> 34:30.032
Je suis là.

34:30.034 --> 34:31.000
[Breathing heavily]

34:31.002 --> 34:33.969
Je suis là pour toi. Tranquille.
On est ensemble. Finalement.

34:38.009 --> 34:39.408
[Screams]

34:40.277 --> 34:42.344
Aah!

34:42.346 --> 34:44.880
[Screams]

34:44.882 --> 34:46.181
No!

34:46.184 --> 34:49.150
[Whimpering]

34:49.152 --> 34:51.020
Doucement.

34:51.022 --> 34:55.690
That's why I need you to see
everything I've done, okay?

34:55.693 --> 34:56.958
Here. Here.

34:56.960 --> 34:58.961
Monty: According to those
files you scanned for me,

34:58.963 --> 35:01.964
the Mossier clan is like
some withering bastard branch

35:01.966 --> 35:03.499
of the Boulanger family tree.

35:03.501 --> 35:05.434
But the Mossiers... or
what's left of them...

35:05.436 --> 35:07.269
they held title to
five separate holdings

35:07.271 --> 35:08.604
on the outskirts of Paris.

35:08.606 --> 35:10.739
From Meaux all the way to Plaisir.

35:10.741 --> 35:13.509
Jack and Clara are getting pretty close
to that one property in Villepinte.

35:13.511 --> 35:16.312
We have lost our sense of history.

35:16.314 --> 35:19.582
They are calling me
the butcher of Paris.

35:19.584 --> 35:22.585
That name was given to Marcel Petiot.

35:22.587 --> 35:25.554
He was a doctor who killed 23 people

35:25.556 --> 35:27.323
during World War II.

35:27.325 --> 35:29.825
<i>He</i> was a butcher.

35:29.827 --> 35:30.926
And <i> moi?</i>

35:30.928 --> 35:33.462
I am... An <i> artiste.</i>

35:33.464 --> 35:38.067
I took flesh and bone
and made them, uh...

35:38.069 --> 35:39.568
Transcendent.

35:39.570 --> 35:43.572
But none of this would
be possible without you.

35:43.574 --> 35:45.741
You are my muse, Amy.

35:45.743 --> 35:50.679
Because of you, I am transcendent.

35:50.681 --> 35:55.417
You've always been special, Paul.

35:55.419 --> 35:56.619
[Chuckles]

35:56.621 --> 35:59.855
But I couldn't see that before you.

35:59.857 --> 36:01.190
I know.

36:01.192 --> 36:04.159
[ <i>Music continues</i> ]

36:04.161 --> 36:06.061
You know...

36:06.063 --> 36:08.230
When I was a little boy,

36:08.232 --> 36:12.468
my father tried to teach
me how to carve the wood.

36:14.338 --> 36:15.504
[Sighs]

36:15.506 --> 36:17.239
He got frustrated

36:17.241 --> 36:21.410
and burned my hand with his cigarette.

36:22.246 --> 36:26.749
Told me I was not his blood.

36:26.751 --> 36:29.485
I... I am so sorry.

36:29.487 --> 36:34.490
Will you please let me go, Paul?

36:34.492 --> 36:36.225
- I can't.
- Yeah.

36:36.227 --> 36:39.061
Yes, you can.

36:39.063 --> 36:41.130
No, no, Amy.

36:41.132 --> 36:45.467
Without you, I am nothing.

36:45.469 --> 36:48.671
I love you, Amy.

36:48.673 --> 36:50.773
<i>Je t'aime.</i>

36:50.775 --> 36:53.042
[Whimpers]

36:53.044 --> 36:59.581
You understand what
I've done, don't you?

36:59.583 --> 37:01.517
I do.

37:01.519 --> 37:02.918
[Chuckles]

37:12.930 --> 37:14.797
♪

37:14.799 --> 37:17.366
How do you like it?

37:17.368 --> 37:18.767
[Shuddered breathing]

37:18.769 --> 37:22.504
♪

37:29.080 --> 37:30.813
Jack, the French national police

37:30.815 --> 37:33.082
have detained Killian
Mossier in Toulouse.

37:33.084 --> 37:35.250
He has confirmed that his
nephew has taken possession

37:35.252 --> 37:36.852
of the property you're heading to now.

37:36.854 --> 37:38.287
Jack: Does he know if his nephew

37:38.289 --> 37:39.722
has stockpiled any other weapons?

37:39.724 --> 37:41.523
He knows that his nephew's crazy.

37:41.525 --> 37:43.292
- I...
- [Shuddered breathing]

37:43.294 --> 37:46.829
I can't believe you did that.

37:46.831 --> 37:49.665
All those women, Paul?

37:49.667 --> 37:52.735
Oh. <i>Je suis désolé.</i>

37:52.737 --> 37:54.603
Oh, sorry?

37:54.605 --> 37:57.206
You're disgusting.

37:57.208 --> 37:58.507
♪

37:58.509 --> 37:59.475
You're sick.

37:59.477 --> 38:01.377
You've always been sick.

38:01.379 --> 38:06.448
♪

38:07.318 --> 38:09.885
Ah bon ?

38:09.887 --> 38:12.388
Huh ?

38:12.390 --> 38:15.758
Et ça ! C'est quoi ça !
C'est quoi !

38:16.994 --> 38:18.594
[Grunting]

38:18.596 --> 38:20.062
♪

38:20.898 --> 38:23.432
<i>Tu es... </i>

38:23.434 --> 38:25.501
<i>une salope... </i>

38:25.503 --> 38:27.069
♪

38:27.071 --> 38:28.670
<i>sans coeur !</i>

38:28.672 --> 38:30.072
♪

38:30.074 --> 38:31.940
[Grunts]

38:31.942 --> 38:33.809
[Groans]

38:33.811 --> 38:37.246
[Breathing heavily]

38:37.248 --> 38:42.718
♪

38:45.923 --> 38:48.123
I'm sorry, Amy.

38:48.125 --> 38:51.193
[Sobbing]

38:51.195 --> 38:52.694
[Gunshot]

38:52.696 --> 38:56.665
♪

38:56.667 --> 38:58.567
[Panting]

38:58.569 --> 39:00.969
♪

39:00.971 --> 39:02.371
Put it down, Paul!

39:02.373 --> 39:03.539
Now!

39:03.541 --> 39:05.274
♪

39:09.447 --> 39:12.614
[Sobbing]

39:12.616 --> 39:15.884
♪

39:19.890 --> 39:23.091
[Woman singing in French]

39:52.590 --> 39:55.858
[Singing continues]

40:15.779 --> 40:16.845
You know what?

40:16.847 --> 40:18.981
This is one time that
I am kind of okay with

40:18.983 --> 40:20.883
the mechanical delay on the jet.

40:20.885 --> 40:23.652
This is a beautiful city.

40:23.654 --> 40:25.187
Yes, it is.

40:25.189 --> 40:27.623
It's hard sometimes to
appreciate the beauty.

40:27.625 --> 40:30.392
Yeah, we got to find it... somehow.

40:30.394 --> 40:34.062
Otherwise, I don't think we
could do the job we need to do.

40:34.064 --> 40:37.366
Yeah, even the darkest night
will end, and the sun will rise.

40:37.368 --> 40:38.901
To beauty...

40:38.903 --> 40:41.570
wherever we may find it.

